---
import AstroIcon from '../../icons/AstroIcon.astro';
---

<header class='text-center mb-5 flex-shrink-0'>
	<h1
		class='text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-3 flex items-center justify-center gap-3'>
		<AstroIcon class='w-8 h-8 md:w-10 md:h-10 mt-2' />
		<span class='text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-[#A855F7]'>
			astroSharedState
		</span>
	</h1>
	<p class='text-gray-300 text-lg max-w-6xl mx-auto leading-relaxed'>
		Experience seamless state sharing between React, SolidJS, Svelte,
		Vue, and Alpine.js components using <strong
			class='text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-[#A855F7]'
			>Nanostores</strong
		> in <strong class='text-orange-400'
			>Astro {Astro.generator.split(' ')[1]}</strong
		>. Each framework manages its own local state while sharing a
		global counter.
	</p>
</header>
